content.description: A Spanish Omelette is a thick omelette cooked with a layer of potato and onion. The best thing about the Spanish omelette or the tortilla española is that you needn’t stop with the staple potato-cheese-onion combination added to the beaten egg. You can have a Spanish omelette with chopped ham, button mushrooms, green peppers or anything else that strikes your fancy. Pune’s Yolkshire version has bell pepper and celery and the potatoes, laced lightly with melted cheese, have a soft, creamy texture. Called The Spaniards Breakfast, it is one of the high points of this cozy little egg-happy eatery

A Parsi favourite, akuri is egg scrambled with onions, coriander and a mix of spices. It’s served slightly runny (the trick, as with all kinds of creamy scrambled eggs, is to cook it with a touch of milk) and tastes best with pao or toasted bread.

You know that delicious, spicy onion-and-tomato omelette you used to wolf down from the food stalls at the railway station? We hate to break it to you, but that was no omelette. Omelettes are folded around the filling while in a frittata, which is a kind of Italian open-faced omelette, the filling and ingredients are stirred into the beaten egg mixture before it is cooked. Fritate are usually lighter and fluffier than omelettes and retain their flavour and texture even when served cold

content.description: We can’t talk about eggs and not mention Vohuman’s Café’s famed cheese omelette. It’s the greasiest and most delightful egg dish in Pune. The waiters serve it with hot toast thats lathered with butter. You can barely decipher where the cheese ends and the egg begins. With this unabashedly high-cholesterol and high-energy dish, one thing is for certain: Vohuman’s Café is not for the faint-hearted.

A chapati spread with egg batter, fried till it’s crispy and then rolled around a filling of either mince, paneer or grated cheese. That’s a baida roti. Shahi Dawats’s serves a Malbari roti coated with egg and served with either cream or spiced mince

content.description: The most amazing thing about egg curry (slit-boiled eggs in gravy) is that you will have a different idea of what it tastes like depending on which part of India you grew up in. The southern states of India like their curries coconut-based, while a typical Bengali egg curry is spicy. The Coconut Grove has three kinds of egg curry on its menu: the Goan, the Mangalorean and the north Indian. The Mangalorean curry, said Chef Bhoja Pujari, is subtler in taste than the North Indian curry, which contains ground spices
